This paper deals with the analysis of social media data to predict high-impact world events. The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to identify events that are likely to have a significant impact on society. The paper also discusses the unique characteristics of high-impact events and how they are adopted by the network. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
